  "biography_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">The compiler of the Collection of Musical Riddles is anonymous. The work dates to Late Antiquity, likely between the 4th and 6th centuries CE, a period marked by the systematization and transmission of Greek musical theory.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">The sole extant work is the Collection of Musical Riddles. This treatise compiles technical problems concerning the principles of musical science.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">This collection is a minor but specific witness to the study of harmonics in late antiquity. It exemplifies a pedagogical genre dedicated to solving technical problems within the established framework of Greek music theory, demonstrating the continued engagement with specialized scientific knowledge during this period.</p>\n</div>",
